sequenceDiagram
    participant Runtime as Caikit Runtime<br/>(consuming app)
    participant Backend as TGISBackend<br/>backend_type="TGIS"
    participant Conn as TGISConnection<br/>gRPC connection manager
    participant LB as GRPCLoadBalancerProxy<br/>DNS-based LB
    participant DNS as DNS Resolver<br/>53/UDP
    participant TGIS as Remote TGIS Server<br/>50055/TCP gRPC

    Note over Runtime, TGIS: Flow 1: Remote TGIS Inference (Production)

    Runtime->>Backend: get_client(model_id)
    Backend->>Conn: get_client()
    Conn->>LB: Create/reuse gRPC channel

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over LB, DNS: DNS Polling (every 10s default)
        LB->>DNS: socket.getaddrinfo()<br/>53/UDP
        DNS-->>LB: IP addresses for TGIS endpoints
        Note over LB: If IPs changed → reconnect channel
    end

    LB->>TGIS: GenerationService.Generate()<br/>gRPC / TLS 1.2+ / mTLS<br/>50055/TCP
    TGIS-->>LB: GenerationResponse
    LB-->>Conn: Response
    Conn-->>Backend: gRPC client stub
    Backend-->>Runtime: Inference result

    Note over Runtime, TGIS: Flow 1b: Streaming Generation

    Runtime->>Backend: get_client(model_id)
    Backend->>Conn: get_client()
    Conn->>LB: Reuse channel
    LB->>TGIS: GenerationService.GenerateStream()<br/>gRPC server-streaming<br/>TLS/mTLS
    loop Stream chunks
        TGIS-->>LB: GenerationResponse (chunk)
        LB-->>Runtime: Streamed chunk
    end

    Note over Runtime, TGIS: Flow 2: Local TGIS Subprocess (Dev/Test)

    participant Subprocess as ManagedTGISSubprocess
    participant LocalTGIS as Local TGIS<br/>localhost

    Runtime->>Backend: get_client(model_id)
    Backend->>Subprocess: launch()
    Subprocess->>LocalTGIS: Fork TGIS process

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over Subprocess, LocalTGIS: Health Check Loop
        loop Until healthy (max retries)
            Subprocess->>LocalTGIS: HTTP GET health<br/>3000/TCP plaintext
            LocalTGIS-->>Subprocess: Health status
        end
    end

    Subprocess->>LocalTGIS: GenerationService.Generate()<br/>gRPC / plaintext<br/>50055/TCP localhost
    LocalTGIS-->>Subprocess: GenerationResponse
    Subprocess-->>Runtime: Inference result

    Note over Runtime, TGIS: Flow 3: Prompt Artifact Loading

    participant FS as Shared Prompt Dir<br/>(filesystem)

    Runtime->>Conn: load_prompt_artifacts(model_id, artifacts)
    Conn->>FS: shutil.copyfile()<br/>Copy prompt vectors
    FS-->>Conn: Files written
    Conn-->>Runtime: Artifacts loaded
